'''Chic Stone''' ([[January 4]], [[1920s|1923]] &ndash; [[July 28]], [[2000]]) was a comic book illustrator who worked on a few issues in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] comic series.

Stone began in the comic industry working on [[Wikipedia:Fawcett Comics|Fawcett Comics]]' [[Wikipedia:Captain Marvel (DC Comics)|''Captain Marvel'']] in the early 1940s. He worked for several publishers through the 1940s including [[Wikipedia:Timely Comics|Timely Comics]] and [[Wikipedia:Lev Gleason Publications|Lev Gleason Publications]], but would leave comics to work as an art director for various magazines as well as doing storyboard work for television commercials. Stone returned to comics in the 1960s to ink [[Wikipedia:Jack Kirby|Jack Kirby's]] pencils regularly at [[Marvel Comics]] on titles such as [[Wikipedia:Fantastic Four|''Fantastic Four'']], [[Wikipedia:X-Men|''X-Men'']], and [[Wikipedia:Thor (comics)|''Thor'']]. He also worked at [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC Comics]] pencilling a few [[Wikipedia:Batman|''Batman'']] stories. In the 1970s and 80s he would work on several titles at [[Wikipedia:Archie Comics|Archie Comics]] on some of their superhero titles as well as their teen humor line of titles.

